ny-asquith-award-for-the-achievement-in-film-music|title=Anthony Asquith Award for Original Film Music in 2001 {{!}} BAFTA Awards|website=awards.bafta.org|access-date=2020-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190911072638/http://awards.bafta.org/award/2001/film/anthony-asquith-award-for-the-achievement-in-film-music|archive-date=11 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[BAFTA Award for Best Cinematography]]\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2001/film/cinematography|title=Cinematography in 2001 {{!}} BAFTA Awards|website=awards.bafta.org|access-date=2020-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402025303/http://awards.bafta.org/award/2001/film/cinematography|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[BAFTA Award for Best Editing]]\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2001/film/editing|title=Editing in 2001 {{!}} BAFTA Awards|website=awards.bafta.org|access-date=2020-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402024834/http://awards.bafta.org/award/2001/film/editing|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[BAFTA Award for Best Sound]]\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2001/film/sound|title=Sound in 2001 {{!}} BAFTA Awards|website=awards.bafta.org|access-date=2020-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402025026/http://awards.bafta.org/award/2001/film/sound|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[British Independent Film Awards]]\n|Best British Independent Film\n|\n|{{Won}}\n|<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/billy-elliot-wins-four-major-titles-at-british-awards-638168.html|title='Billy Elliot' wins four major titles at British awards|date=2000-10-26|website=The Independent|language=en|access-date=2020-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103103038/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/billy-elliot-wins-four-major-titles-at-british-awards-638168.html|archive-date=3 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best Newcomer\n|Jamie Bell\n|{{Won}}\n|<ref name=\":4\" />\n|-\n|Best Director\n|Stephen Daldry\n|{{Won}}\n|<ref name=\":4\" />\n|-\n|Best Screenplay\n|Lee Hall\n|{{Won}}\n|<ref name=\":4\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Golden Globe Awards]]\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Motion Picture \u2013 Drama|Best Motion Picture \u2013 Drama]]\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/1379168/Billy-Elliot-is-nominated-for-Golden-Globe-award.html|title=Billy Elliot is nominated for Golden Globe award|journal=Daily Telegraph|last=Davis|first=Simon|date=2000-12-22|access-date=2020-01-03|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103103031/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/1379168/Billy-Elliot-is-nominated-for-Golden-Globe-award.html|archive-date=3 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actress \u2013 Motion Picture|Best Supporting Actress \u2013 Motion Picture]]\n|Julie Walters|Julie Walters\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2000/dec/22/filmnews.film|title=Billy Elliot listed for Golden Globe award|last=Kelso|first=Paul|date=2000-12-22|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-01-03|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103103026/https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2000/dec/22/filmnews.film|archive-date=3 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Screen Actors Guild Award]]s\n|[[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Male Actor in a Leading Role|Outstanding Performance by a Male Actor in a Leading Role]]\n|Jamie Bell\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/1154689.stm|title=Jamie's dance to fame|date=2001-02-06|access-date=2020-01-03|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103103030/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/1154689.stm|archive-date=3 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Female Actor in a Supporting Role|Outstanding Performance by a Female Actor in a Supporting Role]]\n|Julie Walters\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.sagawards.org/awards/nominees-and-recipients/7th-annual-screen-actors-guild-awards|title=The 7th Annual Screen Actors Guild Awards {{!}} Screen Actors Guild Awards|website=www.sagawards.org|language=en|access-date=2020-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190706041918/https://www.sagawards.org/awards/nominees-and-recipients/7th-annual-screen-actors-guild-awards|archive-date=6 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture|Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture]]\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref name=\":5\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |[[London Film Critics' Circle]]\n|British Newcomer of the Year\n|Julie Walters|Jamie Bell\n|{{Won}}\n|<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/1172629.stm|title=Awards flow for Billy Elliot|date=2001-02-15|access-date=2020-01-03|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103103036/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/1172629.stm|archive-date=3 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|British Producer of the Year\n|Greg Brenman\nJon Finn\n|{{Won}}\n|<ref name=\":6\" />\n|-\n|British Director of the Year\n|Jamie Bell|Stephen Daldry\n|{{Won}}\n|<ref name=\":6\" />\n|-\n|British Film of the Year\n|''Billy Elliot''|\n|{{Won}}\n|<ref name=\":6\" />\n|-\n|British Actress of the Year \n|Stephen Daldry|Julie Walters\n|{{Won}}\n|<ref name=\":6\" />\n|-\n|[[Motovun Film Festival]]\n|Propeller Award\n|''Billy Elliot''|\n|{{Won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://motovunfilmfestival.com/en/motovun-film-festival-has-a-new-cinema-cinema-billy/|title=Motovun Film Festival has a new cinema - Cinema Billy!|date=2019-02-21|website=Motovun Film Festival|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103111053/https://motovunfilmfestival.com/en/motovun-film-festival-has-a-new-cinema-cinema-billy/|archive-date=3 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Stage musical==\n{{main|Billy Elliot the Musical}}\nAfter the film's release, English singer-songwriter [[Elton John]] collaborated with the film's screenwriter [[Lee Hall (playwright)|Lee Hall]] to produce a musical adaptation of the film, which premiered 31 March 2005 at the [[Victoria Palace Theatre]] on the [[West End theatre|West End]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/musicals/a-bluecollar-tale-mines-rich-musical-seam-20100404-rlig.html|title=A blue-collar tale mines rich musical seam|last=Jones|first=Chris|date=2010-04-04|website=The Sydney Morning Herald|language=en|access-date=2020-01-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200102205048/https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/musicals/a-bluecollar-tale-mines-rich-musical-seam-20100404-rlig.html|archive-date=2 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Many of the film's crew took part in the stage production, including director [[Stephen Daldry]] and choreographer [[Peter Darling]]. The musical received positive reviews and ran for over 4,000 performances before closing in April 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.londontheatre.co.uk/reviews/billy-elliot-victoria-palace-theatre-2005|title=Billy Elliot - Victoria Palace Theatre 2005|newspaper=London Theatre Guide|access-date=18 December 2016|date=11 May 2005|last=Brown|first=Peter|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200101130136/https://www.londontheatre.co.uk/reviews/billy-elliot-victoria-palace-theatre-2005|archive-date=1 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/amp/35069692?client=safari|title=Billy Elliot musical dances out of West End|website=[[BBC News]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=11 December 2015|accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* ''[[Brassed Off]]''\n* ''[[The Stars Look Down]]''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n* [http://cinema.com/articles/160/billy-elliot-production-notes.phtml Production notes]\n\n==Further reading==\n* Jacqueline Jones, \"Small Towns and Big Dreams: Meditations on Two Mining-Town Movies\" ''Perspectives on History'' (Feb 2011) 49#2 pp 30\u201331, compares film with \"[[How Green Was My Valley]]\".\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0249462}}\n* {{mojo title|billyelliot}}\n* {{rotten-tomatoes|billy_elliot}}\n* {{metacritic film|billy-elliot}}\n\n{{The Stars Look Down}}\n{{Lee Hall}}\n{{Stephen Daldry}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title= Awards for ''Billy Elliot''\n|list=\n{{BAFTA Best British Film}}\n{{BIFA BestBritishFilm}}\n{{GLAAD Media Award for Outstanding Film \u2013 Wide Release}}\n{{London Film Critics Circle Award for British Film of the Year}}\n{{Empire Award for Best British Film}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Billy Elliot}}\n[[Category:2000 films]]\n[[Category:2000s dance films]]\n[[Category:2000s comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:British films]]\n[[Category:British comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:British coming-of-age films]]\n[[Category:British dance films]]\n[[Category:2000s coming-of-age comedy films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Stephen Daldry]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Stephen Warbeck]]\n[[Category:Best British Film Empire Award winners]]\n[[Category:Films about ballet]]\n[[Category:Films about the labor movement]]\n[[Category:Films set in County Durham]]\n[[Category:Films set in 1984]]\n[[Category:Films set in 1985]]\n[[Category:Films set in 1999]]\n[[Category:Films shot in England]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Northumberland]]\n[[Category:UK miners' strike (1984\u201385)]]\n[[Category:BAFTA winners (films)]]\n[[Category:BBC Films films]]\n[[Category:StudioCanal films]]\n[[Category:Working Title Films films]]\n[[Category:Films adapted into plays]]\n[[Category:Mining in film]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Lee Hall]]\n[[Category:2000s coming-of-age drama films]]\n[[Category:2000 directorial debut films]]\n", "name_user": "Lizzy150", "label": "safe", "comment": "improvements as per GA review", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Billy_Elliot"}
{"title_page": "Emblem of Nagaland", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox coat of arms\n | name = Emblem of Nagaland\n |image = File:Seal of Nagaland.svg\n | image_width = 200\n | middle = \n | middle_width = \n | middle_caption = \n | lesser = \n | lesser_width = \n | lesser_caption = \n | armiger = The [[Government of Nagaland]]\n | year_adopted = 2005\n | crest = \n | torse = \n | shield = [[Gayal|Mithun bison]]\n | supporters = \n | compartment = \n | motto = Unity\n | orders = \n | other_elements = \n | earlier_versions = \n | use = \n}}\n\nThe '''Emblem of Nagaland''' is the official seal of the government of the [[India]]n [[States of India|state]] of [[Nagaland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nagaland.gov.in//|title=Home: Government of Nagaland : Official Portal|website=www.nagaland.gov.in|access-date=14 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181015080215/https://www.nagaland.gov.in/|archive-date=15 October 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>https://www.dreamstime.com/emblem-government-nagaland-india-kohima-january-official-state-stone-surface-image139997655</ref> It was designed by local artist Merimvu Doulo and was officially adopted in August 2005.\n\n==Design==\n\nThe emblem of Nagaland is a circular seal depicting a [[Gayal|Mithun]] bison standing on a green hilly landscape, surrounded by the motto \"Unity\" and the words \"Government of Nagaland\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/home/new-state-logo-in-nagaland-from-aug-15_225509.html|title=New state logo in Nagaland from Aug 15|date=29 June 2005|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/india/kohima-set-to-stamp-out-ashoka/cid/873536|title=Kohima set to stamp out Ashoka|website=www.telegraphindia.com}}</ref>\n\n==Government banner==\nThe Government of Nagaland can be represented by a banner displaying the emblem of the state on a white field.<ref>https://www.thestatesman.com/northeast/road-not-taken-1502785990.html</ref><ref>https://www.officeholidays.com/holidays/india/nagaland/nagaland-state-inauguration-day</ref><ref>https://www.worldstatesmen.org/India_states.html</ref>\n<gallery>\nFile:..Nagaland Flag(INDIA).png|Banner of Nagaland\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n* [[National Emblem of India]]\n* [[List of Indian state emblems]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20181015080215/https://www.nagaland.gov.in/ Government of Nagaland]\n\n[[Category:Government of Nagaland]]\n[[Category:Indian state seals|Nagaland]]\n[[Category:Symbols of Nagaland]]\n\n\n{{India-gov-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox coat of arms\n | name = Emblem of Nagaland\n |image = File:Seal of Nagaland.svg\n | image_width = 200\n | middle = \n | middle_width = \n | middle_caption = \n | lesser = \n | lesser_width = \n | lesser_caption = \n | armiger = The [[Government of Nagaland]]\n | year_adopted = 2005\n | crest = \n | torse = \n | shield = [[Gayal|Mithun bison]]\n | supporters = \n | compartment = \n | motto = Unity\n | orders = \n | other_elements = \n | earlier_versions = \n | use = \n}}\n\nThe '''Emblem of Nagaland''' is the official seal of the government of the [[India]]n [[States of India|state]] of [[Nagaland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nagaland.gov.in//|title=Home: Government of Nagaland : Official Portal|website=www.nagaland.gov.in|access-date=14 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181015080215/https://www.nagaland.gov.in/|archive-date=15 October 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> <ref>https://www.dreamstime.com/emblem-government-nagaland-india-kohima-january-official-state-stone-surface-image139997655</ref> It was designed by local artist Merimvu Doulo and was officially adopted in August 2005.\n\n==Design==\n\nThe emblem of Nagaland is a circular seal depicting a [[Gayal|Mithun]] bison standing on a green hilly landscape, surrounded by the motto \"Unity\" and the words \"Government of Nagaland\". <ref>{{cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/home/new-state-logo-in-nagaland-from-aug-15_225509.html|title=New state logo in Nagaland from Aug 15|date=29 June 2005|publisher=}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/india/kohima-set-to-stamp-out-ashoka/cid/873536|title=Kohima set to stamp out Ashoka|website=www.telegraphindia.com}}</ref> \n\n==Government banner==\nThe Government of Nagaland can be represented by a banner displaying the emblem of the state on a white field. <ref>https://www.thestatesman.com/northeast/road-not-taken-1502785990.html</ref> <ref>https://www.officeholidays.com/holidays/india/nagaland/nagaland-state-inauguration-day</ref> <ref>https://www.worldstatesmen.org/India_states.html</ref>\n<gallery>\nFile:..Nagaland Flag(INDIA).png|Banner of Nagaland\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n* [[National Emblem of India]]\n* [[List of Indian state emblems]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20181015080215/https://www.nagaland.gov.in/ Government of Nagaland]\n\n[[Category:Government of Nagaland]]\n[[Category:Indian state seals|Nagaland]]\n[[Category:Symbols of Nagaland]]\n\n{{India-gov-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Titodutta", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emblem_of_Nagaland"}
{"title_page": "Forever Living Products", "text_new": "{{short description|American multi-level marketing company}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2017}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name                = Forever Living Products International, Inc.\n| logo                = Foreverlivingproducts logo.jpg\n| logo_size           = 220px\n| type                = \n| foundation          = 1978\n| location            = [[Scottsdale, Arizona]], [[United States]]\n| key_people          = [[Rex Maughan]] (Chairman/CEO)</br>Gregg Maughan (President)\n| area_served         = \n| industry            = [[Multi-level marketing]]\n| products            = [[Aloe vera]]- and [[bee]]-based products\n| revenue             = $13.6M <small> (2018) </small>\n| operating_income    = \n| net_income          = \n| parent              = \n| subsid              = Forever Resorts, Aloe Vera of America, Forever Aloe Plantations, Forever Nutraceutical\n| homepage            = {{URL|www.foreverliving.com/}}\n| footnotes           = \n}}\n\n'''Forever Living Products International, Inc.''' (FLPI) is an American [[Privately held company|privately held]] [[multi-level marketing]] (MLM) company based in [[Scottsdale, Arizona|Scottsdale]], [[Arizona]], which manufactures and markets [[aloe vera]]-based drinks and [[bee]]-derived cosmetics, [[dietary supplements]], and personal care products.<ref name=\"Forbes\"/> The company was founded in 1978 by CEO [[Rex Maughan]]. After acquiring the company '''Aloe Vera of America''' by the 1990s,<ref name=\"flabaloeveraofmaerica\"/> the company reported a network of 9.3 million distributors and revenue of $1.7 billion in 2010, and in 2006 they reported having 4,100 employees.<ref name=\"Forbes\"/><ref name=\"flademmert\"/> More than 90% of all of the aloe farming grounds worldwide belong to Forever Living Products.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aloe-medical-group.com/en/aloe-vera/quality-production.html?l=774|title=Quality & Production process - AMGI|website=www.aloe-medical-group.com|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nForever Living was founded in 1978 in [[Tempe, Arizona]]<ref name=FLP/> by Carl Jensen and [[Rex Maughan]].<ref name=\"Forbes\"/> By the 1990s, Maughan had purchased the Texas company Aloe Vera of America, with Aloe Vera of America selling its products to Forever Living for distribution.<ref name=\"flabaloeveraofmaerica\"/> Some journalists have likened the [[multi-level marketing]] business model of Forever Living's distribution system to that of a [[pyramid scheme]].<ref name=\"manilatimes\"/>\n\n[[File:Forever Living in McCormick Ranch in 2007.png|thumb|Forever Living Products headquarters in McCormick Ranch in Arizona in 2007. The company's resort division owns several similar properties.]]\nIn 1983, the company was named No. 6 on [[Inc. (magazine)|''Inc. Magazine'']]'s annual Inc. 500 list of the fastest-growing private companies in the United States.<ref name=\"cmor\"/>\n\nAccording to Arthur Andersen's Top 100, as of 1993, Forever Living Products International was Arizona's second-largest private company.<ref name=\"flaabestkeptsecret\"/> As of August 1995, ''[[Forbes]]'' reported the company's product line included \"deodorants, toothpaste, [[laundry detergent]] and three dozen other products, nearly all of which contain extract of aloe.\"<ref name=\"dmor\"/>\n\nAnnual revenue exceeded $1.15 billion in 2005<ref name=\"Forbes\"/> and Forever Living ended the year with around 150,000 distributors<ref name=\"zfro\"/> and 55 employees.<ref name=\"zffinancier\"/> The following year, Forever Living was listed at No. 340 on the [[Forbes 400]] list, which ranks the largest private companies in the United States. At the time, the company was described as having 4,100 employees and sold its product in 100 countries.<ref name=\"Forbes\"/>\n\nIn 2010, the company reported a revenue of $1.7 billion and a network of 9.3 million distributors.<ref name=\"flademmert\"/> \nThe company was active in over 165 countries as of 2018.<ref name=FLP/> In February 2015, the company announced they had appointed a new management team to \"oversee the affairs of the company in [[Nigeria]].\"<ref name=\"amortidenews\"/>\n\n==Legal==\nIn 1996, upon suggestion of the American authorities, the [[Internal Revenue Service]] (IRS) and the [[National Tax Agency]] of Japan (NTA) initiated a joint audit of Rex and Ruth Maughan and related entities Aloe Vera of America (AVA), Selective Art Inc., FLP International, and FLP Japan for the period of 1991 to 1995.<ref name=\"bcoptexax\"/> In 1997, the NTA imposed a penalty tax of 3.5 billion yen on Forever Living's Japan division for concealing income of 7.7 billion yen over the five-year period.<ref name=\"niflbkyodo\"/> Later that year, AVA, Rex and Ruth Maughan, Maughan Holdings, Gene Yamagata, and Yamagata Holdings<ref name=\"aaloevera\"/> sued the IRS for unauthorized disclosure of tax return information.<ref name=\"niflbkyodo\"/> In the midst of the lawsuit, The IRS asked the NTA to drop its decision against Forever Living, and in 2002, the agency \u201cgrudgingly complied with the IRS's request\u201d, announcing that the penalty tax had been effectively withdrawn.<ref name=\"niflbkyodo\"/> In February 2015, a USA district court ruled that the IRS knowingly provided some false information about AVA to the NTA, in violation of the United States' tax treaty with Japan.<ref name=\"niflasixty\"/> and awarded three of the plaintiffs one thousand dollars each in statutory damages.<ref name=\"niflasixty\"/>\n\nIn 2004 claims made about Forever Living products were found to be in violation of several laws in Hungary related to advertising, registration of nutritional products, and the use of cosmetics as medicinal agents. As a result, the company was fined 60 million HUF (approximately US$280,000).<ref name=\"hun\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gvh.hu/gvh/alpha?do=2&pg=11&m5_doc=3743|title=Hungarian Economic Competition Office fined FLP for 60 million HUF|access-date=November 25, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140110231503/http://www.gvh.hu/gvh/alpha?do=2&pg=11&m5_doc=3743|archive-date=January 10, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn 2007, author [[Richard Bach]] made claims against the company for [[copyright infringement]] and [[trademark infringement]].<ref name=fanfiction/> The lawsuit stated that for over 20 years Forever Living had used the character, storyline, and copyrighted excerpts from the novel ''[[Jonathan Livingston Seagull]]'' to promote its marketing plan, and also used the [[Jonathan Livingston Seagull (film)|motion picture]] and novel as its corporate logo.<ref name=\"copyright\">{{cite web|url=https://scholar.google.com/scholar_case?case=3858152414403488946&hl=en&as_sdt=2&as_vis=1&oi=scholarr|title=Richard BACH, et al., Plaintiffs, v. FOREVER LIVING PRODUCTS U.S., INC., et al., Defendants.}}</ref><ref>[http://www.lawupdates.com/summary/bach_v_forever_living_products_us_inc/ Law Updates: Richard Bach et al]</ref> The claim was satisfied through arbitration,<ref name=\"aforeverseagull\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =Bach v. Forever Living Products US, Inc., 473 F. Supp. 2d 1110 \n| first       =\n| last        =\n| url         =https://scholar.google.com/scholar_case?case=3858152414403488946&hl=en&as_sdt=2&as_vis=1&oi=scholarr\n| newspaper   =\n| publisher   =\n| date        =February 6, 2007\n| accessdate  = May 27, 2015\n}}</ref> and shortly after, Forever Living changed its company logo<ref name=\"bbachsres\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =Bach v. Forever Living Products U.S., Inc. \n| first       =\n| last        =\n| url         =http://www.lawupdates.com/summary/bach_v_forever_living_products_us_inc/ \n| publisher   =Law Updates\n| date        =July 13, 2007\n| accessdate  = May 27, 2015\n}}</ref> from a seagull to an eagle.{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}\n\nIn 2015, Forever Living was criticized by the UK Advertising Standards Authority for making false claims about the health benefits of its products, which were sold as a cure for various diseases ranging from diabetes to Crohn's disease. The company was also warned not to use health professionals in its promotional materials. Subsequently, the UK Medicines And Healthcare Products Regulatory Agency launched an investigation after it was revealed that [[National Health Service|NHS]] staff were moonlighting as sales people.<ref name=\"ASA\">{{cite web |title=ASA Ruling on Forever Living Products (UK) Ltd |url=https://www.asa.org.uk/rulings/forever-living-products-uk-ltd-a15-293201.html |publisher=The Advertising Standards Authority Ltd / The Committee of Advertising Practice |accessdate=September 27, 2018 |date=September 2, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"IML\">{{cite news |title=Forever Living Warned by ASA |url=https://www.insidermedia.com/insider/midlands/146660- |accessdate=September 27, 2018 |publisher=Insider Media Ltd |date=September 1, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"NI_061416\">{{cite web |last1=Harrison-Dunn |first1=Annie |title=ASA puts maca claims to bed following Facebook fallout |url=https://www.nutraingredients.com/Article/2016/06/15/ASA-puts-maca-claims-to-bed-following-Facebook-fallout |website=Nutra Ingredients |accessdate=September 27, 2018 |date=June 14, 2016}}</ref>\n\nBetween 2011 and 2016, Forever Living Products and its associated companies have been sued multiple times in the Superior Court of California by Environmental Research Center (ERC), a California non-profit corporation<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.erc501c3.org/about|title=About {{!}} Environmental Research Center|website=www.erc501c3.org|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref>, for violations of Proposition 65 or the Safe Drinking Water and Toxic Exposure Act.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://webapps.sftc.org/ci/CaseInfo.dll?SessionID=1506D7F9C2B63A224D51B79F777C18B1899F2DB2&URL=https://imgquery.sftc.org/Sha1_newApp/mainpage.aspx?Web_Server=imgquery.sftc.org&MINDS_Server=hoj-imx-01&Category=C&DocID=03370152&Timestamp=20190830164441=dd34204185aacf772936281d521ae5a3d022ebb9|title=ERC v Forever Living 2011|website=webapps.sftc.org|access-date=2019-08-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://webapps.sftc.org/ci/CaseInfo.dll?SessionID=BBFC53B446910BDB6851D8C116CAACA498B23983&URL=https%3A%2F%2Fimgquery.sftc.org%2FSha1_newApp%2Fmainpage.aspx%3FWeb_Server%3Dimgquery.sftc.org%26MINDS_Server%3Dhoj-imx-01%26Category%3DC%26DocID%3D03966920%26Timestamp%3D20190830164146%3D20ecd4605fe945323ab5c28c699529e8e0429389|title=ERC v Forever Living Products 2013|website=webapps.sftc.org|access-date=2019-08-30}}</ref> The ERC alleged that levels of lead in supplements, makeup, drinks, protein shakes, and bee pollen manufactured by Aloe Vera of America and distributed by Forever Living Products contained lead in quantities requiring warnings to consumers. The products identified in the complaints are no longer available for sale in California and some of the products alleged to contain lead including Garcinia Plus, Forever Lite shakes, and Bee Pollen were part of the Clean 9 kit which was marketed as a \"detox\" program.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dietselfhelp.com/clean-9-detox-diet-review-beginners-guide/|title=Clean 9 Detox Diet: The Complete Review and Beginner's Guide|last=Jan 22|first=the Diet Self Help Team {{!}}|last2=Guides {{!}} 0|first2=2019 {{!}} Diet|date=2019-01-22|website=Diet Self Help|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-30}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Business}}\n*[[Old Thong Chai Medical Institution]]\n*[[Nutraceutical]]\n*[[:Category:Forever Resorts]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2|refs=\n \n<ref name=\"zffinancier\">{{cite web|url=http://www.zf.ro/articol_91703/forever_living_products_hopes_to_see_sales_up_in_h2.html |title=Forever Living Products hopes to see sales up in H2|date=August 2006|publisher=Ziarul Financiar|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080804002448/http://www.zf.ro/articol_91703/forever_living_products_hopes_to_see_sales_up_in_h2.html |archivedate = August 4, 2008}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"flaabestkeptsecret\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =No. 2 private company is 'best-kept secret' in state. (Forever Living Products International Inc.) ( in state) \n| first       =Jenni\n| last        =Huston\n| url         =http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/58438913?q&versionId=71446911\n| archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20150620082621/http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/58438913?q&versionId=71446911\n| archive-date=2015-06-20\n| newspaper   =The Business Journal\n| publisher   =Trove\n| date        =November 12, 1993\n| accessdate  =2019-10-04\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"flademmert\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =DSN Global 100: The Top Direct Selling Companies in the World\n| first       =J.M.\n| last        =Emmert\n| url         =http://directsellingnews.com/index.php/view/dsn_global_100_the_top_selling_companies_in_the_world/P1#.VXXsNEr9rw4\n| newspaper   =Direct Selling News\n| publisher   =\n| date        =2011\n| accessdate  = June 6, 2015\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"amortidenews\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =Forever Living Product Gets New Management Team In Nigeria\n| first       =Jon\n| last        =Bilbur\n| url         =http://www.thetidenewsonline.com/2015/02/20/forever-living-product-gets-new-management-team-in-nigeria/\n| newspaper   =[[The Tide News]] Online\n| publisher   =\n| date        =February 20, 2015\n| accessdate  = May 27, 2015\n}}</ref>\n\n<!--unused<ref name=kagolo>{{cite news|last1=Kagolo|first1=Francis|title=Network marketing sucking billions out of Ugandans|url=http://www.newvision.co.ug/news/639919-network-marketing-sucking-billions-out-of-ugandans.html|accessdate=January 29, 2015|work=[[New Vision]]|date=February 17, 2013}}</ref>-->\n\n<ref name=FLP>{{cite web|title=About Forever Living|url=https://www.foreverliving.com/marketing/Page.do;jsessionid=845C6054BA950C88D17D9A53ADCE3A51.tc5-web1?name=about|publisher=www.foreverliving.com|accessdate=January 31, 2015}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Forbes\">{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2006/21/biz_06privates_Forever-Living-Products-Intl_4L21.html|title=The Largest Private Companies: #340 Forever Living Products Intl|year=2006|publisher=forbes.com|accessdate=June 29, 2008}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"flabaloeveraofmaerica\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =ALOE VERA OF AMERICA INC v. UNITED STATES \n| first       =\n| last        =\n| url         =https://caselaw.findlaw.com/us-9th-circuit/1088862.html\n| newspaper   =\n| publisher   =Case Law\n| date        =July 30, 2009\n| accessdate  = June 6, 2015\n}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"dmor\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =The aloe juice man. (Forever Living Products International)\n| first       =Christopher\n| last        =Palmeri\n| url         =http://business.highbeam.com/392705/article-1G1-17390818/aloe-juice-man\n| archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20150530032056/http://business.highbeam.com/392705/article-1G1-17390818/aloe-juice-man\n| url-status    =dead\n| archive-date =May 30, 2015\n| newspaper   =[[Forbes]]\n| publisher   =Business: Highbeam\n| date        =August 14, 1995\n| accessdate  = May 27, 2015\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"manilatimes\">{{cite news| title=A very thin line between multilevel marketing and pyramid schemes| url=http://www.culteducation.com/group/1256-general-assembly/8460-a-very-thin-line-between-multilevel-marketing-and-pyramid-schemes-.html| author = Max de Leon| date=April 28, 2003| accessdate=April 21, 2014}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"cmor\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =Going Their Way - Whatever else catapulted them to the peak, it wasn't conformity to the norms of business\n| first       =Tom\n| last        =Richman\n| url         =http://www.inc.com/magazine/19831201/7965.html \n| publisher   =[[Inc.com]]\n| date        =December 1, 1983\n| accessdate  = May 27, 2015\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"niflasixty\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =Ariz. Judge Docks U.S. $3,000 For Disclosing Taxpayer Info \n| first       =Eric\n| last        =Kroh\n| url         =http://www.law360.com/articles/620920/ariz-judge-docks-u-s-3-000-for-disclosing-taxpayer-info\n| newspaper   =\n| publisher   =law360.com\n| date        =February 11, 2015\n| accessdate  = May 27, 2015\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=fanfiction>{{cite book|last=Schwabach|first=Aaron|title=Fanfiction and Copyright|year=2011|publisher=Ashgate|isbn=978-0-7546-7903-5|pages=39\u201340|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YBV6KcYOuQAC&pg=PA39&lpg=PA39#v=onepage&q&f=false}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"niflbkyodo\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =Tax agency takes back penalty tax on U.S.-affiliate firm.\n| first       =\n| last        =\n| url         =http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Tax+agency+takes+back+penalty+tax+on+U.S.-affiliate+firm.-a089843804\n| newspaper   =\n| publisher   =Kyodo News International, Inc.\n| date        =July 26, 2002\n| accessdate  = May 27, 2015\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"aaloevera\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =376 F. 3d 960 - Aloe Vera of America Inc v. United States\n| first       =\n| last        =\n| url         =http://openjurist.org/376/f3d/960/aloe-vera-of-america-inc-v-united-states\n| newspaper   =\n| publisher   =OpenJurist\n| date        =July 19, 2004\n| accessdate  = May 27, 2015\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"bcoptexax\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =United States Held Liable for Making False Statements to Foreign Tax Authority\n| first       =Charles W.\n| last        =Cope\n| url         =http://www.copetax.com/united-states-liable-for-making-false-statements \n| publisher   =copetax.com\n| date        =February 2015\n| accessdate  = May 27, 2015\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"zfro\">{{cite web|url=http://www.zf.ro/articol_91703/forever_living_products_hopes_to_see_sales_up_in_h2.html |title=Forever Living Products hopes to see sales up in H2|date=August 2006|publisher=Ziarul Financiar|accessdate=June 29, 2008 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080804002448/http://www.zf.ro/articol_91703/forever_living_products_hopes_to_see_sales_up_in_h2.html |archivedate = August 4, 2008}}</ref>\n\n<!--\n\n<ref name=\"emor\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =Forever Living Products Review 2011\n| first       =Ted\n| last        =Nuyten\n| url         =http://www.businessforhome.org/2011/08/forever-living-products-review-2011/\n| newspaper   =\n| publisher   =Business for Home\n| date        =August 9, 2011\n| accessdate  = February 25, 2015\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"fmorgrowthace\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =Forever Living Products International Inc. History\n| url         =http://www.fundinguniverse.com/company-histories/forever-living-products-international-inc-history/\n| publisher   =Funding Universe\n| date        =\n| accessdate  = February 25, 2015\n}} (original source used by author: ''International Directory of Company Histories'', Vol. 17. St. James Press, 1997.)</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"\">{{cite news\n| title       = \n| first       = \n| last        = \n| url         = \n| newspaper   = \n| publisher   = \n| date        = \n| accessdate  = July 6, 2014\n}}</ref>\n\n-->\n\n}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Forever Living Products}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20150810094514/https://www.foreverliving.com/marketing/Home.do ForeverLiving.com]\n\n{{Multi-level marketing}}\n\n[[Category:Personal selling]]\n[[Category:Privately held companies based in Arizona]]\n[[Category:American companies established in 1978]]\n[[Category:Retail companies established in 1978]]\n[[Category:Personal care brands]]\n[[Category:Skin care]]\n[[Category:Multi-level marketing companies]]\n[[Category:Cosmetics brands]]\n[[Category:Forever Living Products]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American multi-level marketing company}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2017}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Forever Living Products International, Inc.\n| logo = Foreverlivingproducts logo.jpg\n| logo_size = 220px\n| type = \n| foundation = 1978\n| location = [[Scottsdale, Arizona]], [[United States]]\n| key_people = [[Rex Maughan]], founder\n| area_served = \n| industry = [[Multi-level marketing]]\n| products = [[Aloe vera]]- and [[bee]]-based products\n| revenue = $13.6M <small> (2018) </small>\n| operating_income = \n| net_income = \n| num_employees = 76 <small>(2006)</small>\n| parent = \n| subsid = Forever Resorts, Aloe Vera of America, Forever Aloe Plantations, Forever Nutraceutical\n| homepage = {{URL|www.foreverliving.com/}}\n| footnotes = \n}}\n\n'''Forever Living Products International, Inc.''' (FLPI) is an American [[Privately held company|privately held]] [[multi-level marketing]] (MLM) company based in [[Scottsdale, Arizona|Scottsdale]], [[Arizona]], which manufactures and markets [[aloe vera]]-based drinks and [[bee]]-derived cosmetics, [[dietary supplements]], and personal care products.<ref name=\"Forbes\"/> The company was founded in 1978 by CEO [[Rex Maughan]]. After acquiring the company '''Aloe Vera of America''' by the 1990s,<ref name=\"flabaloeveraofmaerica\"/> the company reported a network of 9.3 million distributors and revenue of $1.7 billion in 2010, and in 2006 they reported having 4,100 employees.<ref name=\"Forbes\"/><ref name=\"flademmert\"/>\n\n==History==\nForever Living was founded in 1978 in [[Tempe, Arizona]]<ref name=FLP/> by Carl Jensen and [[Rex Maughan]].<ref name=\"Forbes\"/> By the 1990s, Maughan had purchased the Texas company Aloe Vera of America, with Aloe Vera of America selling its products to Forever Living for distribution.<ref name=\"flabaloeveraofmaerica\"/> Some journalists have likened the [[multi-level marketing]] business model of Forever Living's distribution system to that of a [[pyramid scheme]].<ref name=\"manilatimes\"/>\n\n[[File:Forever Living in McCormick Ranch in 2007.png|thumb|Forever Living Products headquarters in McCormick Ranch in Arizona in 2007. The company's resort division owns several similar properties.]]\nIn 1983, the company was named No. 6 on [[Inc. (magazine)|''Inc. Magazine'']]'s annual Inc. 500 list of the fastest-growing private companies in the United States.<ref name=\"cmor\"/>\n\nAccording to Arthur Andersen's Top 100, as of 1993, Forever Living Products International was Arizona's second-largest private company.<ref name=\"flaabestkeptsecret\"/> As of August 1995, ''[[Forbes]]'' reported the company's product line included \"deodorants, toothpaste, [[laundry detergent]] and three dozen other products, nearly all of which contain extract of aloe.\"<ref name=\"dmor\"/>\n\nAnnual revenue exceeded $1.15 billion in 2005<ref name=\"Forbes\"/> and Forever Living ended the year with around 150,000 distributors<ref name=\"zfro\"/> and 55 employees.<ref name=\"zffinancier\"/> The following year, Forever Living was listed at No. 340 on the [[Forbes 400]] list, which ranks the largest private companies in the United States. At the time, the company was described as having 4,100 employees and sold its product in 100 countries.<ref name=\"Forbes\"/>\n\nIn 2010, the company reported a revenue of $1.7 billion and a network of 9.3 million distributors.<ref name=\"flademmert\"/> \nThe company was active in over 165 countries as of 2018.<ref name=FLP/> In February 2015, the company announced they had appointed a new management team to \"oversee the affairs of the company in [[Nigeria]].\"<ref name=\"amortidenews\"/>\n\n==Legal==\nIn 1996, upon suggestion of the American authorities, the [[Internal Revenue Service]] (IRS) and the [[National Tax Agency]] of Japan (NTA) initiated a joint audit of Rex and Ruth Maughan and related entities Aloe Vera of America (AVA), Selective Art Inc., FLP International, and FLP Japan for the period of 1991 to 1995.<ref name=\"bcoptexax\"/> In 1997, the NTA imposed a penalty tax of 3.5 billion yen on Forever Living's Japan division for concealing income of 7.7 billion yen over the five-year period.<ref name=\"niflbkyodo\"/> Later that year, AVA, Rex and Ruth Maughan, Maughan Holdings, Gene Yamagata, and Yamagata Holdings<ref name=\"aaloevera\"/> sued the IRS for unauthorized disclosure of tax return information.<ref name=\"niflbkyodo\"/> In the midst of the lawsuit, The IRS asked the NTA to drop its decision against Forever Living, and in 2002, the agency \u201cgrudgingly complied with the IRS's request\u201d, announcing that the penalty tax had been effectively withdrawn.<ref name=\"niflbkyodo\"/> In February 2015, a USA district court ruled that the IRS knowingly provided some false information about AVA to the NTA, in violation of the United States' tax treaty with Japan.<ref name=\"niflasixty\"/> and awarded three of the plaintiffs one thousand dollars each in statutory damages.<ref name=\"niflasixty\"/>\n\nIn 2004 claims made about Forever Living products were found to be in violation of several laws in Hungary related to advertising, registration of nutritional products, and the use of cosmetics as medicinal agents. As a result, the company was fined 60 million HUF (approximately US$280,000).<ref name=\"hun\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gvh.hu/gvh/alpha?do=2&pg=11&m5_doc=3743|title=Hungarian Economic Competition Office fined FLP for 60 million HUF|access-date=November 25, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140110231503/http://www.gvh.hu/gvh/alpha?do=2&pg=11&m5_doc=3743|archive-date=January 10, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn 2007, author [[Richard Bach]] made claims against the company for [[copyright infringement]] and [[trademark infringement]].<ref name=fanfiction/> The lawsuit stated that for over 20 years Forever Living had used the character, storyline, and copyrighted excerpts from the novel ''[[Jonathan Livingston Seagull]]'' to promote its marketing plan, and also used the [[Jonathan Livingston Seagull (film)|motion picture]] and novel as its corporate logo.<ref name=\"copyright\">{{cite web|url=https://scholar.google.com/scholar_case?case=3858152414403488946&hl=en&as_sdt=2&as_vis=1&oi=scholarr|title=Richard BACH, et al., Plaintiffs, v. FOREVER LIVING PRODUCTS U.S., INC., et al., Defendants.}}</ref><ref>[http://www.lawupdates.com/summary/bach_v_forever_living_products_us_inc/ Law Updates: Richard Bach et al]</ref> The claim was satisfied through arbitration,<ref name=\"aforeverseagull\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =Bach v. Forever Living Products US, Inc., 473 F. Supp. 2d 1110 \n| first       =\n| last        =\n| url         =https://scholar.google.com/scholar_case?case=3858152414403488946&hl=en&as_sdt=2&as_vis=1&oi=scholarr\n| newspaper   =\n| publisher   =\n| date        =February 6, 2007\n| accessdate  = May 27, 2015\n}}</ref> and shortly after, Forever Living changed its company logo<ref name=\"bbachsres\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =Bach v. Forever Living Products U.S., Inc. \n| first       =\n| last        =\n| url         =http://www.lawupdates.com/summary/bach_v_forever_living_products_us_inc/ \n| publisher   =Law Updates\n| date        =July 13, 2007\n| accessdate  = May 27, 2015\n}}</ref> from a seagull to an eagle.{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}\n\nIn 2015, Forever Living was criticized by the UK Advertising Standards Authority for making false claims about the health benefits of its products, which were sold as a cure for various diseases ranging from diabetes to Crohn's disease. The company was also warned not to use health professionals in its promotional materials. Subsequently, the UK Medicines And Healthcare Products Regulatory Agency launched an investigation after it was revealed that [[National Health Service|NHS]] staff were moonlighting as sales people.<ref name=\"ASA\">{{cite web |title=ASA Ruling on Forever Living Products (UK) Ltd |url=https://www.asa.org.uk/rulings/forever-living-products-uk-ltd-a15-293201.html |publisher=The Advertising Standards Authority Ltd / The Committee of Advertising Practice |accessdate=September 27, 2018 |date=September 2, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"IML\">{{cite news |title=Forever Living Warned by ASA |url=https://www.insidermedia.com/insider/midlands/146660- |accessdate=September 27, 2018 |publisher=Insider Media Ltd |date=September 1, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"NI_061416\">{{cite web |last1=Harrison-Dunn |first1=Annie |title=ASA puts maca claims to bed following Facebook fallout |url=https://www.nutraingredients.com/Article/2016/06/15/ASA-puts-maca-claims-to-bed-following-Facebook-fallout |website=Nutra Ingredients |accessdate=September 27, 2018 |date=June 14, 2016}}</ref>\n\nBetween 2011 and 2016, Forever Living Products and its associated companies have been sued multiple times in the Superior Court of California by Environmental Research Center (ERC), a California non-profit corporation<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.erc501c3.org/about|title=About {{!}} Environmental Research Center|website=www.erc501c3.org|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref>, for violations of Proposition 65 or the Safe Drinking Water and Toxic Exposure Act.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://webapps.sftc.org/ci/CaseInfo.dll?SessionID=1506D7F9C2B63A224D51B79F777C18B1899F2DB2&URL=https://imgquery.sftc.org/Sha1_newApp/mainpage.aspx?Web_Server=imgquery.sftc.org&MINDS_Server=hoj-imx-01&Category=C&DocID=03370152&Timestamp=20190830164441=dd34204185aacf772936281d521ae5a3d022ebb9|title=ERC v Forever Living 2011|website=webapps.sftc.org|access-date=2019-08-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://webapps.sftc.org/ci/CaseInfo.dll?SessionID=BBFC53B446910BDB6851D8C116CAACA498B23983&URL=https%3A%2F%2Fimgquery.sftc.org%2FSha1_newApp%2Fmainpage.aspx%3FWeb_Server%3Dimgquery.sftc.org%26MINDS_Server%3Dhoj-imx-01%26Category%3DC%26DocID%3D03966920%26Timestamp%3D20190830164146%3D20ecd4605fe945323ab5c28c699529e8e0429389|title=ERC v Forever Living Products 2013|website=webapps.sftc.org|access-date=2019-08-30}}</ref> The ERC alleged that levels of lead in supplements, makeup, drinks, protein shakes, and bee pollen manufactured by Aloe Vera of America and distributed by Forever Living Products contained lead in quantities requiring warnings to consumers. The products identified in the complaints are no longer available for sale in California and some of the products alleged to contain lead including Garcinia Plus, Forever Lite shakes, and Bee Pollen were part of the Clean 9 kit which was marketed as a \"detox\" program.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dietselfhelp.com/clean-9-detox-diet-review-beginners-guide/|title=Clean 9 Detox Diet: The Complete Review and Beginner's Guide|last=Jan 22|first=the Diet Self Help Team {{!}}|last2=Guides {{!}} 0|first2=2019 {{!}} Diet|date=2019-01-22|website=Diet Self Help|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-30}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Business}}\n*[[Old Thong Chai Medical Institution]]\n*[[Nutraceutical]]\n*[[:Category:Forever Resorts]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2|refs=\n \n<ref name=\"zffinancier\">{{cite web|url=http://www.zf.ro/articol_91703/forever_living_products_hopes_to_see_sales_up_in_h2.html |title=Forever Living Products hopes to see sales up in H2|date=August 2006|publisher=Ziarul Financiar|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080804002448/http://www.zf.ro/articol_91703/forever_living_products_hopes_to_see_sales_up_in_h2.html |archivedate = August 4, 2008}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"flaabestkeptsecret\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =No. 2 private company is 'best-kept secret' in state. (Forever Living Products International Inc.) ( in state) \n| first       =Jenni\n| last        =Huston\n| url         =http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/58438913?q&versionId=71446911\n| archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20150620082621/http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/58438913?q&versionId=71446911\n| archive-date=2015-06-20\n| newspaper   =The Business Journal\n| publisher   =Trove\n| date        =November 12, 1993\n| accessdate  =2019-10-04\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"flademmert\">\n{{cite news\n| title       =DSN Global 100: The Top Direct Selling Companies in the World\n| first       =J.M.\n| last        =Emmert\n| url         =http://directsellingnews.com/index.php/view/dsn_global_100_the_top_selling_companies_in_the_world/P1#.VXXsNEr9rw4\n| newspaper   =Direct Selling News\n| publisher   =\n| date     