{"title_page": "Nehoiu", "text_new": "{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = town\n|county                 = Buz\u0103u\n|population_total       = auto\n|image_skyline=Ro bz nehoiu entrance.jpg\n|image_caption=Nehoiu, seen from the road to [[Buz\u0103u]]\n|official_name=Nehoiu\n|image_shield=\n|image_map = Nehoiu jud Buzau.png\n|map_caption = Location in Buz\u0103u County\n|leader_name=Ionu\u021b Milea<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.2016bec.ro/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/SIAL2016_P_Lista_Moc-2.xlsx |title=Results of the 2016 local elections |publisher=Central Electoral Bureau |accessdate=2020-04-03 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|leader_party=PSD\n|area_total_km2=\n|coordinates            = {{coord|45|21|11|N|26|18|18|E|region:RO|display=inline,title}}\n|website=\n}}\n\n'''Nehoiu''' ({{IPA-ro|ne\u02c8hoju}}) is a town in [[Buz\u0103u County]], [[Romania]], with a population of 11,631. Wood processing is the local main economic activity. The town has a lumbermill since the early 20th century.\n\nThe town administers nine villages: B\u00e2sca Rozilei, Chirle\u0219ti, Curm\u0103tura, Lunca Priporului, Ml\u0103jet, Nehoia\u0219u, P\u0103ltineni, St\u0103nila and Vine\u021bi\u0219u.\n{{Historical populations\n|source = Census data\n|1992 |12664\n|2002 |12650\n|2011 |9959\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Nehoiu}}\n* [http://www.itinerar.ro/Muntii/loc-bz_en.htm#1 Nehoiu tourist information (in English)]\n\n{{Buz\u0103u County}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in Romania]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Buz\u0103u County]]\n\n{{Buz\u0103u-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = town\n|county                 = Buz\u0103u\n|population_total       = auto\n|image_skyline=Ro bz nehoiu entrance.jpg\n|image_caption=Nehoiu, seen from the road to [[Buz\u0103u]]\n|official_name=Nehoiu\n|image_shield=\n|image_map = Nehoiu jud Buzau.png\n|map_caption = Location in Buz\u0103u County\n|leader_name=Ionu\u021b Milea\n|leader_party=PSD\n|area_total_km2=\n|coordinates            = {{coord|45|21|11|N|26|18|18|E|region:RO|display=inline,title}}\n|website=\n}}\n\n'''Nehoiu''' ({{IPA-ro|ne\u02c8hoju}}) is a town in [[Buz\u0103u County]], [[Romania]], with a population of 11,631. Wood processing is the local main economic activity. The town has a lumbermill since the early 20th century.\n\nThe town administers nine villages: B\u00e2sca Rozilei, Chirle\u0219ti, Curm\u0103tura, Lunca Priporului, Ml\u0103jet, Nehoia\u0219u, P\u0103ltineni, St\u0103nila and Vine\u021bi\u0219u.\n{{Historical populations\n|source = Census data\n|1992 |12664\n|2002 |12650\n|2011 |9959\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Nehoiu}}\n* [http://www.itinerar.ro/Muntii/loc-bz_en.htm#1 Nehoiu tourist information (in English)]\n\n{{Buz\u0103u County}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in Romania]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Buz\u0103u County]]\n\n{{Buz\u0103u-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Markussep", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nehoiu"}
{"title_page": "Emblem of Maharashtra", "text_new": "{{Infobox coat of arms\n | name = Emblem of Maharashtra\n | image = File:Seal of Maharashtra.png\n | image_width = 200\n | middle = \n | middle_width = \n | middle_caption = \n | lesser = \n | lesser_width = \n | lesser_caption = \n | armiger = The [[Government of Maharashtra]]\n | year_adopted = \n | crest = \n | torse = \n | shield = [[Diya (lamp)|Samai diya lamp]]\n | supporters = \n | compartment = \n | motto = The glory of Maharashtra will grow like the first day moon. It will be worshipped by the world and will shine only for the well being of people.\n | orders = \n | other_elements = [[Nelumbo nucifera|Lotus blossoms]]\n | earlier_versions = \n | use = \n}}\nThe '''Emblem of Maharashtra''' is the [[official seal]] of the government of the [[India]]n [[States of India|state]] of [[Maharashtra]].<ref>http://maharashtra.gov.in/</ref>\n\n==Design==\nThe emblem is a circular seal depicting a [[Diya (lamp)|Samai diya lamp]] surrounded by 16 [[Nelumbo nucifera|lotus blossoms]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hubert-herald.nl/BhaMaharashtra.htm |title=Maharashtra |publisher=Hubert-herald.nl |date= |accessdate=2020-03-15}}</ref> Between the Samai lamp and lotus blossoms is a motto in the [[Marathi language]] that translates as \"The glory of Maharashtra will grow like the first day moon. It will be worshipped by the world and will shine only for the well being of people\". The motto is based on one found on the \"Rajmudra\" (royal seal) used by 17th-century [[Maratha Empire|Maratha]] king [[Chhatrapati Shivaji]].<ref>https://punemirror.indiatimes.com/pune/cover-story/state-govts-spin-on-chhatrapati-shivajis-rajmudra-draws-public-ire/articleshow/65015105.cms</ref>\n\n==Historic emblems==\n<gallery>\nFile:Royal seals of Shivaji.jpg|Royal seals (\"Rajmudra\") used by [[Chhatrapati Shivaji]] and the [[Maratha Empire]]\nFile:Indian Embassy in London wall plaque (5).jpg|Emblem of the [[Bombay Presidency]] during the [[British Raj]]\nFile:Emblem of Bombay State.png|Emblem of the former [[Bombay State]]\n</gallery>\n\n==Government banner==\nThe Government of Maharashtra can be represented by a banner displaying the emblem of the state on a white field.<ref>https://www.dreamstime.com/maharashtra-state-india-flag-textile-cloth-fabric-waving-top-sunrise-mist-fog-beautiful-maharashtra-state-india-flag-image127909976</ref><ref>https://www.worldstatesmen.org/India_states.html</ref>\n<gallery>\nFile:..Maharashtra Flag(INDIA).png|Banner of Maharashtra\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n* [[National Emblem of India]]\n* [[List of Indian state emblems]]\n* [[Coat of arms of Mumbai]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Government of Maharashtra]]\n[[Category:Indian state seals|Maharashtra]]\n[[Category:Symbols of Maharashtra]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox coat of arms\n | name = Emblem of Maharashtra\n | image = File:Seal of Maharashtra.png\n | image_width = 200\n | middle = \n | middle_width = \n | middle_caption = \n | lesser = \n | lesser_width = \n | lesser_caption = \n | armiger = The [[Government of Maharashtra]]\n | year_adopted = \n | crest = \n | torse = \n | shield = [[Diya (lamp)|Samai diya lamp]]\n | supporters = \n | compartment = \n | motto = The glory of Maharashtra will grow like the first day moon. It will be worshipped by the world and will shine only for the well being of people.\n | orders = \n | other_elements = [[Nelumbo nucifera|Lotus blossoms]]\n | earlier_versions = \n | use = \n}}\nThe '''Emblem of Maharashtra''' is the [[official seal]] of the government of the [[India]]n [[States of India|state]] of [[Maharashtra]]. <ref>http://maharashtra.gov.in/</ref> \n\n==Design==\nThe emblem is a circular seal depicting a [[Diya (lamp)|Samai diya lamp]] surrounded by 16 [[Nelumbo nucifera|lotus blossoms]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hubert-herald.nl/BhaMaharashtra.htm |title=Maharashtra |publisher=Hubert-herald.nl |date= |accessdate=2020-03-15}}</ref> Between the Samai lamp and lotus blossoms is a motto in the [[Marathi language]] that translates as \"The glory of Maharashtra will grow like the first day moon. It will be worshipped by the world and will shine only for the well being of people\". The motto is based on one found on the \"Rajmudra\" (royal seal) used by 17th-century [[Maratha Empire|Maratha]] king [[Chhatrapati Shivaji]]. <ref>https://punemirror.indiatimes.com/pune/cover-story/state-govts-spin-on-chhatrapati-shivajis-rajmudra-draws-public-ire/articleshow/65015105.cms</ref>\n\n==Historic emblems==\n<gallery>\nFile:Royal seals of Shivaji.jpg|Royal seals (\"Rajmudra\") used by [[Chhatrapati Shivaji]] and the [[Maratha Empire]]\nFile:Indian Embassy in London wall plaque (5).jpg|Emblem of the [[Bombay Presidency]] during the [[British Raj]]\nFile:Emblem of Bombay State.png|Emblem of the former [[Bombay State]]\n</gallery>\n\n==Government banner==\nThe Government of Maharashtra can be represented by a banner displaying the emblem of the state on a white field. <ref>https://www.dreamstime.com/maharashtra-state-india-flag-textile-cloth-fabric-waving-top-sunrise-mist-fog-beautiful-maharashtra-state-india-flag-image127909976</ref> <ref>https://www.worldstatesmen.org/India_states.html</ref>\n<gallery>\nFile:..Maharashtra Flag(INDIA).png|Banner of Maharashtra\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n* [[National Emblem of India]]\n* [[List of Indian state emblems]]\n* [[Coat of arms of Mumbai]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Government of Maharashtra]]\n[[Category:Indian state seals|Maharashtra]]\n[[Category:Symbols of Maharashtra]]\n", "name_user": "Titodutta", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emblem_of_Maharashtra"}
{"title_page": "Jean-Baptiste Mondino", "text_new": "'''Jean-Baptiste Mondino''' (born [[Aubervilliers]], [[France]] on July 21, 1949) is a French [[fashion photographer]]<ref>[http://www.artnet.com/galleries/Exhibitions.asp?gid=423991310&cid=102331 M+B : Past and future exhibitions<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and [[music video director]]. He has directed music videos for [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]], [[David Bowie]], [[Sting (musician)|Sting]], [[Bj\u00f6rk]], [[Don Henley]], [[Neneh Cherry]], [[Axel Bauer]] and [[Les Rita Mitsouko]].<ref>{{mvdbase|space=person|id=C813|title=Jean-Baptiste Mondino|access-date=January 28, 2017}}</ref>  Mondino has also photographed the covers and album packaging for the [[Marianne Faithfull]] albums ''[[Before The Poison]]'' (2005) and ''[[Easy Come, Easy Go (Marianne Faithfull album)|Easy Come, Easy Go]]''  (2008), [[Shakespear's Sister]]'s ''[[Hormonally Yours]]'' (1992), [[Alain Bashung]]'s ''[[Osez Jos\u00e9phine]]'' (1991), ''[[Chatterton (album)|Chatterton]]'' (1994), [[Myl\u00e8ne Farmer]]'s ''D\u00e9sob\u00e9issance'' (2018) and [[Prince (musician)|Prince]]'s ''[[Lovesexy]]'' (1988).\n\nThe video for [[Don Henley]]'s \"[[The Boys of Summer (song)|The Boys of Summer]]\", which Mondino directed,<ref>[http://www.mvdbase.com/video.php?id=12946 Credits] for the \"Boys of Summer\" video.</ref> swept the [[MTV Video Music Awards]] in 1985, winning \"[[MTV Video Music Award for Video of the Year|Best Video]]\", \"[[MTV Video Music Award for Best Direction|Best Direction]]\", \"[[MTV Video Music Award for Best Art Direction|Best Art Direction]]\" and \"[[MTV Video Music Award for Best Cinematography|Best Cinematography]]\". This video paired him with compatriot cinematographer, [[Pascal Leb\u00e8gue]], with whom he would later shoot several other notable music videos in black and white, such as \"[[Russians (song)|Russians]]\" for [[Sting (musician)|Sting]] and \"[[Justify My Love]]\" for [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]].\n\n==Music video filmography==\n<!--[[Music video director]] links directly here.-->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Film\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Artist\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1981\n| \"Paradis\"\n| [[Alain Chamfort]]\n| \n|-\n| \"Little Darlin'\"\n| Sheila\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1983\n| \"Quelqu'un comme toi\"\n| [[Taxi Girl]]\n|\n|-\n| \"Soleil, soleil\"\n| [[Ahmed Fakroun]]\n|\n|-\n| \"La danse des mots\" \n| Mon Dino \n| aka Jean-Baptiste Mondino\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1984\n| \"Cargo\"\n| [[Axel Bauer]]\n|\n|-\n| \"Un autre monde\"\n| [[T\u00e9l\u00e9phone]]\n|\n|-\n| \"[[The Boys of Summer (song)|The Boys of Summer]]\" \n| [[Don Henley]]\n| Won [[MTV Video Music Award for Video of the Year|Video of the Year]], [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Direction|Best Direction]],  <br>[[MTV Video Music Award for Best Art Direction|Best Art Direction]], and [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Cinematography|Best Cinematography]]<br> at the 1985 [[MTV Video Music Awards]].\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1985\n| \"[[Slave to Love]]\" & \"[[Don't Stop the Dance]]\"\n| [[Bryan Ferry]]\n|\n|-\n| \"[[Downtown Train]]\" \n| [[Tom Waits]]\n|\n|-\n| \"[[Russians (song)|Russians]]\" \n| [[Sting (musician)|Sting]]\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1986\n| \"[[Each Time You Break My Heart]]\" \n| [[Nick Kamen]]\n|\n|-\n| \"[[Open Your Heart (Madonna song)|Open Your Heart]]\" \n| [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]]\n| \n|-\n| \"Wood Beez\" \n| [[Scritti Politti]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\"| 1987\n| \"C'est comme \u00e7a\"\n| [[Les Rita Mitsouko]]\n|\n|-\n| \"You Owe Me Some Kind of Love\" \n| [[Chris Isaak]]\n|\n|-\n| \"[[Never Let Me Down (David Bowie song)|Never Let Me Down]]\" \n| [[David Bowie]]\n|\n|-\n| \"To Be Reborn\" \n| [[Boy George]]\n|\n|-\n| \"Mia Bocca\" \n| [[Jill Jones]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1988\n| \"Qu'est-ce que t'es belle\" \n| [[Catherine Ringer]] & [[Marc Lavoine]]\n| \n|-\n| \"[[I Wish U Heaven]]\" \n| [[Prince (musician)|Prince]]\n|\n|-\n| \"How to Do That\" \n| [[Jean-Paul Gaultier]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1989\n| \"Be\" \n| [[Lenny Kravitz]]\n|\n|-\n| \"[[Manchild (song)|Manchild]]\" \n| [[Neneh Cherry]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1990\n| \"[[I've Got You Under My Skin]]\" \n| Neneh Cherry \n| \n|-\n| \"[[Justify My Love]]\" \n| Madonna\n| \n|-\n| \"Tandem\" \n| [[Vanessa Paradis]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1991\n| \"Sorry About the Weather\" \n| [[Mark Curry (rock musician)|Mark Curry]]\n| \n|-\n| \"Osez Jos\u00e9phine\" \n| [[Alain Bashung]]\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1992\n| \"Volutes\" \n| Alain Bashung\n| \n|-\n| \"Born on the Wrong Side of Town\" \n| [[Jaye Muller|J. (Jaye Muller)]]\n| \n|-\n| \"Rhythm Is Love\" \n| [[Keziah Jones]] \n| \n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1993\n| \"L'ennemi dans la glace\" \n| Alain Chamfort \n|\n|-\n| \"Buddy X\" \n| Neneh Cherry \n| \n|-\n| \"Natural High\" \n| Vanessa Paradis\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\"| 1994\n| \"Ma petite entreprise\" \n| Alain Bashung\n|\n|-\n| \"[[Violently Happy]]\" \n| [[Bj\u00f6rk]]\n|\n|-\n| \"If That's Your Boyfriend (He Wasn't Last Night)\" \n| [[Meshell Ndegeocello]]\n|\n|-\n| \"Les amants\" \n| Les Rita Mitsouko\n|\n|-\n| \"S\u00e9quelles\" \n| [[MC Solaar]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1995\n| \"[[Wonderful Shadow]]\" \n| [[Tanita Tikaram]]\n|\n|-\n| \"[[Human Nature (Madonna song)|Human Nature]]\" \n| Madonna\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1996\n| \"[[Love Don't Live Here Anymore]]\" \n| Madonna\n|\n|-\n| \"Time\"  \n| [[China Moses]]\n|\n|-\n| \"Kootchi\" \n| Neneh Cherry\n|\n|-\n| 1998\n| \"Tout le monde\" \n| [[Zazie]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2000\n| \"Naive Song\"  \n| [[Mirwais Ahmadza\u00ef]]\n|\n|-\n| \"[[Don't Tell Me (Madonna song)|Don't Tell Me]]\" \n| Madonna\n| Nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best Music Video]]. <br>Two nominations at [[2001 MTV Video Music Awards]]. \n|-\n| 2003\n| \"[[Hollywood (Madonna song)|Hollywood]]\"\n| Madonna\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2007\n| \"Sing Sing\"