ks==\n*[http://www.jeanbaptistemondino.com/ Official website]\n*[http://mondinomonde.byethost13.com/ Mondino Monde: The Work Of Jean-Baptiste Mondino]\n*{{IMDb name|id=0597761|name=Jean-Baptiste Mondino}}\n*[http://www.macguff.fr/index.php?lang=fr&j=showoneimage&id=70#1138191962 Watch Mondino's video for ''C'est comme \u00e7a'' (Les Rita Mitsouko)]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070519203027/http://www.lumiere.com/fashion/96/01/mondino/interview.html Interview with Lumiere magazine]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mondino, Jean-Baptiste}}\n[[Category:1949 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Aubervilliers]]\n[[Category:Fashion photographers]] <!-- Independent evidence, please. -->\n[[Category:French music video directors]]\n[[Category:French photographers]] <!-- Independent evidence, please. -->\n", "text_old": "'''Jean-Baptiste Mondino''' (born [[Aubervilliers]], [[France]] on July 21, 1949) is a French [[fashion photographer]]<ref>[http://www.artnet.com/galleries/Exhibitions.asp?gid=423991310&cid=102331 M+B : Past and future exhibitions<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and [[music video director]]. He has directed music videos for [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]], [[David Bowie]], [[Sting (musician)|Sting]], [[Bj\u00f6rk]], [[Don Henley]], [[Neneh Cherry]], [[Axel Bauer]] and [[Les Rita Mitsouko]].<ref>{{mvdbase|space=person|id=C813|title=Jean-Baptiste Mondino|access-date=January 28, 2017}}</ref>  Mondino has also photographed the covers and album packaging for the [[Marianne Faithfull]] albums ''[[Before The Poison]]'' (2005) and ''[[Easy Come, Easy Go (Marianne Faithfull album)|Easy Come, Easy Go]]''  (2008), [[Shakespear's Sister]]'s ''[[Hormonally Yours]]'' (1992), [[Alain Bashung]]'s ''[[Osez Jos\u00e9phine]]'' (1991), ''[[Chatterton (album)|Chatterton]]'' (1994), [[Myl\u00e8ne Farmer]]'s ''D\u00e9sob\u00e9issance'' (2018) and [[Prince (musician)|Prince]]'s ''[[Lovesexy]]'' (1988).\n\nThe video for [[Don Henley]]'s \"[[The Boys of Summer (song)|The Boys of Summer]]\", which Mondino directed,<ref>[http://www.mvdbase.com/video.php?id=12946 Credits] for the \"Boys of Summer\" video.</ref> swept the [[MTV Video Music Awards]] in 1985, winning \"[[MTV Video Music Award for Video of the Year|Best Video]]\", \"[[MTV Video Music Award for Best Direction|Best Direction]]\", \"[[MTV Video Music Award for Best Art Direction|Best Art Direction]]\" and \"[[MTV Video Music Award for Best Cinematography|Best Cinematography]]\". This video paired him with compatriot cinematographer, [[Pascal Leb\u00e8gue]], with whom he would later shoot several other notable music videos in black and white, such as \"[[Russians (song)|Russians]]\" for [[Sting (musician)|Sting]] and \"[[Justify My Love]]\" for [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]].\n\n==Music video filmography==\n<!--[[Music video director]] links directly here.-->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Film\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Artist\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1981\n| \"Paradis\"\n| [[Alain Chamfort]]\n| \n|-\n| \"Little Darlin'\"\n| Sheila\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1983\n| \"Quelqu'un comme toi\"\n| [[Taxi Girl]]\n|\n|-\n| \"Soleil, soleil\"\n| [[Ahmed Fakroun]]\n|\n|-\n| \"La danse des mots\" \n| Mon Dino \n| aka Jean-Baptiste Mondino\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1984\n| \"Cargo\"\n| [[Axel Bauer]]\n|\n|-\n| \"Un autre monde\"\n| [[T\u00e9l\u00e9phone]]\n|\n|-\n| \"[[The Boys of Summer (song)|The Boys of Summer]]\" \n| [[Don Henley]]\n| Won [[MTV Video Music Award for Video of the Year|Video of the Year]], [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Direction|Best Direction]],  <br>[[MTV Video Music Award for Best Art Direction|Best Art Direction]], and [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Cinematography|Best Cinematography]]<br> at the 1985 [[MTV Video Music Awards]].\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1985\n| \"[[Slave to Love]]\" & \"[[Don't Stop the Dance]]\"\n| [[Bryan Ferry]]\n|\n|-\n| \